infotexts.entitydescription.ekdockyard_reactor_min: Usable device for generating electrical power. A successfull miniaturization of small-modular-reactor architecture, compact enough to see use on some shuttle craft for extended range.

infotexts.entitydescription.ekdockyard_fusionfuel_: Conventional fusile material which predates the colonies. However due to the immense colony resource demands, production of viable tritium deuterium fuel on industrial scale is still very costly.

A mixture of pressurized oxygenite vapor and lithium dust. The process takes advantage of oxygenite's unique metaphysical properties, producing an easy-fusing fuel but relatively low effective output.

A naturally occuring but thinly scattered fusile material. Sometimes found in large veins with other radioactive minerals or within' icy asteroids, making it a relatively easy fuel source to come by - until recently.
Experimental fusile matter supply powered by an alien cell. Capable of producing a very energetic reaction, however its exact function is not well understood.
infotexts.entitydescription.ekdockyard_reactorfusi: Miniaturized magnetic-confinement fusion reactor utilizing a spherical Tokamak configuration. Capable of using a wide variety of fuel mixtures.
